criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. are ≥18 years of age;

          2. have a BMI between 25.0-49.9 kg/m2;

          3. Participants also will have no serious, unstable co-morbidity that would make
             participation in a diet and PA intervention difficult or risky;

          4. live in or near the Columbia, SC area;

          5. have access to the Internet, a computer, a smartphone, and a valid email address;

          6. are not pregnant or planning on becoming pregnant;

          7. are not currently enrolled in a weight-loss study or are actively taking weight-loss
             medications; and

          8. are willing and able to participate fully in the study for a period of one year.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. congestive heart failure;

          2. chronic renal failure;

          3. chronic liver disease, including alcoholic cirrhosis;

          4. a diagnosis of cancer within the past year, except for non-melanoma skin cancer;

          5. actively receiving cancer treatment;

          6. poor performance status (e.g., non-ambulatory); or

          7. life expectancy <3 years, on hospice, nursing home or other institutionalized care.
             Individuals will be screened at the clinical practice site(s) to ensure that they meet
             all of the eligibility criteria and have none of the ineligibility criteria.
